Niger state government on Friday returned 43 passengers back to their state of origin as the state records it third case of COVID19 has in Minna the state capital. This was disclosed by the Commissioner for Health and Hospital Services, Dr Muhammad Makusidi Makusidi explained that the COVID19 patient who is over 30 years is a driver from Kano State and was driving-pass Minna towards Kano when he was intercepted for flouting the Niger State COVID19 movement restriction order. The Commissioner said the driver was tried by the mobile court and quarantined, where his sample was taken to Abuja for test and it returned positive.
